Use the standard library
This is how to can_arrange of arr:
   Remember that n is arr's length
   Remember that i is diff of n and 2
   Remember that neg1 is diff of 0 and 1
   Do this diff of n and 1 times:
      Remember that j is sum of i and 1
      When item i in arr is more than item j in arr, then:
         The answer is i
      End when
      Decrease i
   End do
   The answer is neg1
Now you know
>>> can_arrange of [1, 2, 4, 3, 5] 
3
>>> can_arrange of [1, 2, 3] 
-1
>>> can_arrange of [1, 2, 4, 3, 5] 
3